@iSazonov, Looks like it's a breaking change and not the bug - [#7424](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/7424)
Before PowerShell Core 7.1,  the path is resolved relative to the current shell location(not changed for Get-Module, Import-Module). Now, for the statement `using module`, the path is resolved  relative to the current script. 

I think  the documentation should be updated to describe the new behavior.

Ah, I see you run from a root folder.

@al-cheb Please open new issue in https://github.com/MicrosoftDocs/PowerShell-Docs

